    "summary": "After receiving my Ph.D. from the Department of Cognitive Neuroscience at Maastricht University, I continued my work there as a postdoctoral researcher within the human brain project (HBP). \n\nMy research interests fall within three categories. The first is visuomotor integration with a focus on the development of  large-scale models of eye movement control and attention. The second concerns population receptive field mapping. The third is the role of structural hubs for the globally coordinated integration of specialized brain regions.\n\n",
